msgctxt "an9.33:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "4. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Anupubbavihārasamāpattisutta "
msgstr "33. The Nine Progressive Meditative Attainments "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.411, sc1
#. VAR: Navayimā, bhikkhave → nava bhikkhave (?)
msgctxt "an9.33:1.1"
msgid "“Navayimā, bhikkhave, anupubbavihārasamāpattiyo desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha … pe … "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the nine progressive meditative attainments … "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.2"
msgid "katamā ca, bhikkhave, nava anupubbavihārasamāpattiyo? "
msgstr "And what are the nine progressive meditative attainments? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.33:1.3"
msgid "Yattha kāmā nirujjhanti, ye ca kāme nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti, ‘addhā te āyasmanto nicchātā nibbutā tiṇṇā pāraṅgatā tadaṅgenā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Where sensual pleasures cease, and those who have thoroughly ended sensual pleasures meditate, I say: ‘Clearly those venerables are desireless, extinguished, crossed over, and gone beyond in that respect.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.4"
msgid "‘Kattha kāmā nirujjhanti, ke ca kāme nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti—"
msgstr "If someone should say, ‘I do not know or see where sensual pleasures cease’, "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.5"
msgid "ahametaṃ na jānāmi ahametaṃ na passāmī’ti, iti yo evaṃ vadeyya, so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "they should be told: "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.6"
msgid "‘idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, it’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.7"
msgid "Ettha kāmā nirujjhanti, te ca kāme nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s where sensual pleasures cease.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.8"
msgid "Addhā, bhikkhave, asaṭho amāyāvī ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinandeyya anumodeyya; "
msgstr "Clearly someone who is not devious or deceitful would approve and agree with that statement. "

msgctxt "an9.33:1.9"
msgid "‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā namassamāno pañjaliko payirupāseyya. (1) "
msgstr "They’d say ‘Good!’ and bowing down, they’d pay homage with joined palms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an9.33:2.1"
msgid "Yattha vitakkavicārā nirujjhanti, ye ca vitakkavicāre nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti, ‘addhā te āyasmanto nicchātā nibbutā tiṇṇā pāraṅgatā tadaṅgenā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Where the placing of the mind and keeping it connected cease, and those who have thoroughly ended the placing of the mind and keeping it connected meditate, I say: ‘Clearly those venerables are desireless, extinguished, crossed over, and gone beyond in that respect.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.2"
msgid "‘Kattha vitakkavicārā nirujjhanti, ke ca vitakkavicāre nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti—"
msgstr "If someone should say, ‘I do not know or see where the placing of the mind and keeping it connected cease’, "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.3"
msgid "ahametaṃ na jānāmi ahametaṃ na passāmī’ti, iti yo evaṃ vadeyya, so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "they should be told: "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.4"
msgid "‘idhāvuso, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.5"
msgid "ettha vitakkavicārā nirujjhanti, te ca vitakkavicāre nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s where the placing of the mind and keeping it connected cease.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.6"
msgid "Addhā, bhikkhave, asaṭho amāyāvī ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinandeyya anumodeyya; "
msgstr "Clearly someone who is not devious or deceitful would approve and agree with that statement. "

msgctxt "an9.33:2.7"
msgid "‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā namassamāno pañjaliko payirupāseyya. (2) "
msgstr "They’d say ‘Good!’ and bowing down, they’d pay homage with joined palms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.412, sc3
msgctxt "an9.33:3.1"
msgid "Yattha pīti nirujjhati, ye ca pītiṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti, ‘addhā te āyasmanto nicchātā nibbutā tiṇṇā pāraṅgatā tadaṅgenā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Where rapture ceases, and those who have thoroughly ended rapture meditate, I say: ‘Clearly those venerables are desireless, extinguished, crossed over, and gone beyond in that respect.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.2"
msgid "‘Kattha pīti nirujjhati, ke ca pītiṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti—"
msgstr "If someone should say, ‘I do not know or see where rapture ceases’, "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.3"
msgid "ahametaṃ na jānāmi ahametaṃ na passāmī’ti, iti yo evaṃ vadeyya, so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "they should be told: "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.4"
msgid "‘idhāvuso, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant, with the fading away of rapture, enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss”. "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.5"
msgid "ettha pīti nirujjhati, te ca pītiṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s where rapture ceases.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.6"
msgid "Addhā, bhikkhave, asaṭho amāyāvī ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinandeyya anumodeyya; "
msgstr "Clearly someone who is not devious or deceitful would approve and agree with that statement. "

msgctxt "an9.33:3.7"
msgid "‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā namassamāno pañjaliko payirupāseyya. (3) "
msgstr "They’d say ‘Good!’ and bowing down, they’d pay homage with joined palms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an9.33:4.1"
msgid "Yattha upekkhāsukhaṃ nirujjhati, ye ca upekkhāsukhaṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti, ‘addhā te āyasmanto nicchātā nibbutā tiṇṇā pāraṅgatā tadaṅgenā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Where equanimous bliss ceases, and those who have thoroughly ended equanimous bliss meditate, I say: ‘Clearly those venerables are desireless, extinguished, crossed over, and gone beyond in that respect.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.2"
msgid "‘Kattha upekkhāsukhaṃ nirujjhati, ke ca upekkhāsukhaṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharanti—"
msgstr "If someone should say, ‘I do not know or see where equanimous bliss ceases’, "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.3"
msgid "ahametaṃ na jānāmi ahametaṃ na passāmī’ti, iti yo evaṃ vadeyya, so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "they should be told: "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.4"
msgid "‘idhāvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.5"
msgid "ettha upekkhāsukhaṃ nirujjhati, te ca upekkhāsukhaṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s where equanimous bliss ceases.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.6"
msgid "Addhā, bhikkhave, asaṭho amāyāvī ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinandeyya anumodeyya; "
msgstr "Clearly someone who is not devious or deceitful would approve and agree with that statement. "

msgctxt "an9.33:4.7"
msgid "‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā namassamāno pañjaliko payirupāseyya. (4) "
msgstr "They’d say ‘Good!’ and bowing down, they’d pay homage with joined palms. "

