msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that “space is infinite”, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "an9.33:5.5"
msgid "Ettha rūpasaññā nirujjhati, te ca rūpasaññaṃ nirodhetvā nirodhetvā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s where perceptions of form cease.’ "

msgctxt "an9.33:5.6"
msgid "Addhā, bhikkhave, asaṭho amāyāvī ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinandeyya anumodeyya; "
msgstr "Clearly someone who is not devious or deceitful would approve and agree with that statement. "

